UNITED STATES of America v. Lawrence McCORMICK, etc. No. 5071. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. May 22, 1934. Dwight H. Green, of Chicago, 111., for the United States. Edward H. S. Martin, of Chicago, 111., for appellee.

Before ALSCHULER, SPARKS, and FITZHENRY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellee, it is ordered and adjudged by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed for failure of the appellant to file a brief.
